{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "updatedAt": "2026-06-20T18:27:27.708Z",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Self-correction chains"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " are a specialized prompt chaining pattern where the model "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "critiques and revises its own output"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " in a loop, iteratively improving quality through self-refinement. This technique reduces hallucinations and improves accuracy by encouraging the model to reflect on its output, identify flaws, and fix them."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Think of it as "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "giving the model a \"second chance\" to do better"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " by asking it to critique and improve its own work."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What Self-Correction Chains Are"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Diagram for Self-Correction Chains",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Self-Refinement Prompting:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " This method prompts the LLM to critique and revise its own response. After generating an initial answer, the prompt instructs the model to reflect on its output, identify flaws or inaccuracies, and improve upon it."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Self-correction is more than refinement:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " These methods typically involve instructing models to "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "revise their initially generated answers by leveraging self-correction prompts"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "The core mechanism:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Step 1: Generate initial answer \u2192 Output 1\nStep 2: Critique Output 1 \u2192 Identify flaws\nStep 3: Revise based on critique \u2192 Output 2 (improved)\nStep 4: (Optional) Repeat critique \u2192 revise loop"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why Self-Correction Chains Work"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "1. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Reduces Hallucinations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Using prompting techniques, like Chain-of-Thought and Self-Refinement, can reduce the likelihood of LLM hallucinations"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Encouraging models to generate intermediate reasoning steps helps prevent unsupported or fabricated statements"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "2. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Improves Accuracy"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Self-refinement can be implemented as a multi-turn conversation or a single expanded prompt"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "By requiring the model to reflect on its output and fix errors, accuracy improves significantly."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "3. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Increases Transparency"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Chain-of-Thought explanations give users more insight into the model's internal logic, improving trust and auditability"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You can see both the initial answer AND the critique, making the reasoning process transparent."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "4. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Enables Iterative Improvement"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "We propose Iter-CoT, which enhances LLMs' reasoning performance by integrating iterative bootstrapping to self-correct the reasoning chains in demonstrations"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The iterative loop allows the model to progressively improve quality."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Self-Correction Chain Patterns"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pattern 1: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Single Loop (Critique \u2192 Revise)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "One iteration of critique and revision:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prompt 1: Generate initial answer\n\u2192 Output 1: Initial response\n\nPrompt 2: Critique Output 1\n\u2192 Output 2: List of flaws\n\nPrompt 3: Revise based on critique\n\u2192 Output 3: Improved response"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Example: Code Review"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Step 1: \"Write a Python function to calculate Fibonacci numbers\"\n\u2192 Output 1: Initial implementation\n\nStep 2: \"Review this code [Output 1] for bugs, performance issues, and edge cases\"\n\u2192 Output 2: Critique identifying issues\n\nStep 3: \"Fix all issues identified [Output 2] in this code [Output 1]\"\n\u2192 Output 3: Corrected implementation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pattern 2: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Multi-Loop (Iterative Refinement)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Multiple iterations until quality threshold:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prompt 1 \u2192 Output 1 \u2192 Critique \u2192 Revise \u2192 Output 2 \u2192 Critique \u2192 Revise \u2192 Output 3 \u2192 ... \u2192 Final"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Example: Essay Writing"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Step 1: \"Write a 500-word essay on climate change\"\n\u2192 Output 1: Initial essay\n\nStep 2: \"Critique this essay [Output 1]: Is it clear? Well-structured? Factually accurate?\"\n\u2192 Output 2: Critique feedback\n\nStep 3: \"Revise this essay [Output 1] based on feedback [Output 2]\"\n\u2192 Output 3: Revised essay\n\nStep 4: \"Critique this revised essay [Output 3]: Are the improvements sufficient?\"\n\u2192 Output 4: Second critique\n\nStep 5: \"Revise again based on second critique [Output 4]\"\n\u2192 Output 5: Final polished essay"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pattern 3: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Self-Consistency with Voting"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Generate multiple versions, then select the best:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Generate N versions \u2192 Critique all \u2192 Select best \u2192 Final answer"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Example: Multiple Solutions"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Step 1A: \"Solve this math problem: 15 \u00d7 24\"\n\u2192 Output 1A: Solution A (360)\n\nStep 1B: \"Solve this math problem: 15 \u00d7 24\" (different approach)\n\u2192 Output 1B: Solution B (360)\n\nStep 1C: \"Solve this math problem: 15 \u00d7 24\" (yet another approach)\n\u2192 Output 1C: Solution C (350)\n\nStep 2: \"Compare these solutions [Output 1A + 1B + 1C] and select the correct one\"\n\u2192 Output 2: Selected solution (360) + reasoning"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pattern 4: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Plan \u2192 Execute \u2192 Verify"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Three-stage self-correction:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Step 1: Plan the solution\n\u2192 Output 1: Plan\n\nStep 2: Execute the plan\n\u2192 Output 2: Execution\n\nStep 3: Verify the result\n\u2192 Output 3: Verification + corrections if needed"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Example: Research Task"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Step 1: \"Plan a research approach to analyze market trends for SaaS products\"\n\u2192 Output 1: Research plan\n\nStep 2: \"Execute this research plan [Output 1] to gather data\"\n\u2192 Output 2: Research findings\n\nStep 3: \"Verify these findings [Output 2]: Are they accurate? Complete? Reliable?\"\n\u2192 Output 3: Verification + corrections"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pattern 5: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Refinement with Constraints"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Iterative improvement with specific quality criteria:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Generate \u2192 Critique against constraints \u2192 Revise \u2192 Repeat"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Example: Marketing Copy"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Step 1: \"Write marketing copy for our new SaaS product\"\n\u2192 Output 1: Initial copy\n\nStep 2: \"Critique this copy [Output 1] against these constraints:\n- Maximum 100 words\n- Include 3 key benefits\n- Use active voice\n- No jargon\"\n\u2192 Output 2: Constraint violations identified\n\nStep 3: \"Revise this copy [Output 1] to meet all constraints [Output 2]\"\n\u2192 Output 3: Revised copy meeting constraints\n\nStep 4: \"Verify revised copy [Output 3] meets all constraints\"\n\u2192 Output 4: Final verification"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Real-World Self-Correction Examples"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Example 1: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Code Quality Improvement"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Step 1: Generate initial code\nprompt_1 = \"Write a Python function to sort a list of dictionaries by a key\"\n\u2192 output_1 = \"\"\"\ndef sort_dicts(data, key):\n    return sorted(data, key=lambda x: x[key])\n\"\"\"\n\n# Step 2: Critique the code\nprompt_2 = f\"\"\"\nReview this code:\n{output_1}\n\nIdentify:\n1. Bugs or errors\n2. Performance issues\n3. Edge cases not handled\n4. Style improvements\n\"\"\"\n\u2192 output_2 = \"\"\"\n1. No bugs - code is correct\n2. Performance: O(n log n) - acceptable\n3. Edge cases: Doesn't handle missing keys, empty list\n4. Style: Add type hints, docstring\n\"\"\"\n\n# Step 3: Revise based on critique\nprompt_3 = f\"\"\"\nFix all issues identified:\n{output_2}\n\nIn this code:\n{output_1}\n\"\"\"\n\u2192 output_3 = \"\"\"\ndef sort_dicts(data: list[dict], key: str) -> list[dict]:\n    '''Sort a list of dictionaries by a key.\n    \n    Args:\n        data: List of dictionaries\n        key: Key to sort by\n        \n    Returns:\n        Sorted list\n        \n    Raises:\n        KeyError: If key doesn't exist in any dictionary\n    '''\n    if not data:\n        return []\n    return sorted(data, key=lambda x: x[key])\n\"\"\""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Result:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " Code went from basic to production-ready with error handling, type hints, and documentation."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Example 2: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Math Problem Solving"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Step 1: Generate initial solution\nprompt_1 = \"Solve: If a train travels 60 miles in 1.5 hours, what's its speed?\"\n\u2192 output_1 = \"Speed = 40 mph\"\n\n# Step 2: Show reasoning and verify\nprompt_2 = f\"\"\"\nReview this solution:\n{output_1}\n\nShow your reasoning step by step:\n1. What formula do you use?\n2. Plug in the numbers\n3. Calculate\n4. Verify the answer makes sense\n\"\"\"\n\u2192 output_2 = \"\"\"\nStep 1: Speed = Distance \u00f7 Time\nStep 2: Distance = 60 miles, Time = 1.5 hours\nStep 3: Speed = 60 \u00f7 1.5 = 40 mph\nStep 4: Verification: 40 mph \u00d7 1.5 hours = 60 miles \u2713\nAnswer is correct.\n\"\"\"\n\n# Step 3: Final answer with full explanation\nprompt_3 = f\"\"\"\nBased on this reasoning:\n{output_2}\n\nProvide the final answer with full explanation.\n\"\"\"\n\u2192 output_3 = \"\"\"\nThe train's speed is 40 mph.\n\nFull explanation:\n- Formula: Speed = Distance \u00f7 Time\n- Distance: 60 miles\n- Time: 1.5 hours\n- Calculation: 60 \u00f7 1.5 = 40 mph\n- Verification: 40 mph \u00d7 1.5 hours = 60 miles \u2713\n\"\"\""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Result:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " Went from just the answer to a full, verified solution with reasoning."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Example 3: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Content Quality Improvement"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Step 1: Generate initial content\nprompt_1 = \"Write a product description for our new SaaS analytics tool\"\n\u2192 output_1 = \"\"\"\nOur new analytics tool helps you track metrics. It's fast and easy to use.\nTry it today!\n\"\"\"\n\n# Step 2: Critique against quality standards\nprompt_2 = f\"\"\"\nCritique this product description:\n{output_1}\n\nEvaluate against:\n1. Is it compelling?\n2. Does it explain benefits clearly?\n3. Is it specific enough?\n4. Does it have a strong call to action?\n\"\"\"\n\u2192 output_2 = \"\"\"\n1. Not compelling - generic language\n2. Benefits unclear - \"fast and easy\" is vague\n3. Too specific - no features, no metrics\n4. Weak CTA - \"Try it today\" is generic\nIssues: Needs more detail, specific benefits, stronger CTA\n\"\"\"\n\n# Step 3: Revise based on critique\nprompt_3 = f\"\"\"\nRewrite this description addressing all issues:\n{output_2}\n\nOriginal:\n{output_1}\n\"\"\"\n\u2192 output_3 = \"\"\"\nTransform your data decisions with Analytics Pro \u2014 the SaaS tool that delivers real-time insights in under 5 seconds.\n\n\u2713 Track 50+ metrics automatically\n\u2713 Generate reports in 1 click\n\u2713 Spot trends before they happen\n\nCompanies using Analytics Pro see 30% faster decision-making.\n\nStop guessing with your data. Start making confident decisions. Get your free 14-day trial today!\n\"\"\""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Result:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " Went from generic 2-sentence description to compelling, specific product copy with benefits and strong CTA."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best Practices for Self-Correction Chains"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "1. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Be Specific About What to Critique"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Prompt-based techniques can reduce hallucinations in Large Language Model (LLM) outputs by encouraging more structured reasoning and iterative self-correction"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Define clear criteria for critique:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "\"Critique against these constraints:\n- Maximum 100 words\n- Include 3 key benefits\n- Use active voice\n- No jargon\""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "2. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Use Chain-of-Thought in Critique"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Chain-of-Thought Prompting: This technique guides LLMs to break down their reasoning into intermediate steps before producing a final answer. By requiring the model to \"think aloud,\" it encourages deeper processing of the prompt and increases output accuracy"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "\"Show your reasoning step by step:\n1. What formula do you use?\n2. Plug in the numbers\n3. Calculate\n4. Verify the answer makes sense\""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "3. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Don't Limit to One Loop"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "We propose Iter-CoT, which enhances LLMs' reasoning performance by integrating iterative bootstrapping to self-correct the reasoning chains in demonstrations"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Multiple iterations can significantly improve quality."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "4. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Separate Critique from Revision"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "It helps if you design two different prompts where the first prompt is responsible for extracting relevant quotes to answer a question and a second prompt takes as input the quotes and original document to answer a given question"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Keep critique and revision separate for clarity."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "5. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Include Verification Step"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Reduces Hallucinations and Inaccuracies: Encouraging models to generate intermediate reasoning steps helps prevent unsupported or fabricated statements"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Always verify the revised output meets the original requirements."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Why they work:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "\n1. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Reduces hallucinations"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Prevents unsupported statements\n2. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Improves accuracy"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Model fixes its own errors\n3. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Increases transparency"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 See critique + revision process\n4. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Enables iterative improvement"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Progressive quality gains"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Five patterns:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "\n1. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Single Loop"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Critique \u2192 Revise (one iteration)\n2. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Multi-Loop"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Multiple iterations until threshold\n3. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Self-Consistency"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Generate N versions, select best\n4. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Plan \u2192 Execute \u2192 Verify"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Three-stage refinement\n5. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Refinement with Constraints"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Iterative with quality criteria"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Best practices:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "\n1. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Be specific about critique"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Define clear criteria\n2. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Use CoT in critique"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 \"Think aloud\" reasoning\n3. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Don't limit to one loop"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Multiple iterations\n4. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Separate critique from revision"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Clear prompts\n5. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Include verification"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Ensure requirements met"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Self-Refinement Prompting prompts the LLM to critique and revise its own response, identifying flaws or inaccuracies and improving upon it"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}